// TEST: parse_if_condition_requires_parens
// EXPECT: error E2030 at 19:6
//
// Q-diag-structure-misc (b): an `if` whose condition is not parenthesized used
// to fall into the generic E2000 "expected `(`" catch-all (via the parser's
// `expect`), which named the missing token but neither the violated rule nor
// the fix — so the purpose-built parens-required diagnostic (E2030) was
// unreachable for `if`. The parser now detects the missing `(` at the `if`
// condition directly and emits E2030 with an actionable note ("wrap the
// condition in parentheses: `if (cond) { ... }`"). Bock requires `if (cond)`
// with parentheses (spec §5 / §3.2).
//
// The diagnostic points at the offending token after `if` (the bare condition
// `ready`), at 19:6. Recovery keeps parsing the condition, so the single
// E2030 is the only diagnostic for this root cause (no trailing "expected `)`"
// noise).

fn main() -> Void {
  if ready {
    println("go")
  }
}
